00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Here's what science actually says about checkpoint inhibitors.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:10,000
Checkpoint inhibitors are a groundbreaking approach in immunotherapy, designed to unleash the body's immune system against cancer.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
But how do they work?

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:18,400
They block proteins that keep immune cells in check, allowing them to attack tumors more effectively.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:25,600
Research shows promising results, yet many patients don’t respond, raising questions about why some do and others don’t.

6
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:30,800
Ongoing studies aim to uncover these mysteries, potentially leading to more effective treatments.

7
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,800
Want to learn more about how our bodies fight cancer?

